	Upstaged by Uma    
	 Los Angeles, Nov. 21 (PTI): Actress Uma Thurman is all set to replace Nicole Kidman as the leading lady opposite Twilight star Robert Pattinson in their new film Bel Ami.      
	Although Kidman was never booked officially for the film, an offer was made to her which did not work out. Now, Kill Bill actress Thurman will star in the film which is an adaptation of Guy de Maupassants short story of the same name, reports MTV.com.     
	Cruz crush    
	London (PTI): Actress Kate Hudson has said that her six-year-old son Ryder has developed a crush on her Nine co-star Penelope Cruz. The 30-year-old actress admits that Ryder took a liking to Cruz when Hudson was filming Nine with the Spanish siren. Ryder would say to me: I saw Penelope in the lobby today. You could see that he recognised what a beautiful woman she is. Hes so cute!, Hudson said.                                                                                                                                                       
